X.org 7.2 release has been delayed more than a month, which gave us more time to fix build failures, to work on a few runtime issues and to determine the easiest way to upgrade from 6.9 to 7.2 (mostly with the help of people on the
freebsd-x11@ mailing list
). Everything is in a rather good shape but there's still a little amount of work to do. The merge of new ports is most likely to happen before the end of January.
